        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:18PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 318 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Woolum, or 11 miles northwest of Clinton, moving northeast at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brock Creek Campground...         Thola...
Kay...                            Rupert...
Rocky Hill...                     Landis...
Dennard...                        Dabney...
Timbo...                          Botkinburg...
Gunner Pool Campground...         Crabtree...
Barkshed Campground...            Mountain Man Trailhead...
Harriet...                        Push Mountian...
Newnata...                        Fifty-Six...
Advance...                        Elba...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
central and north central Arkansas.</instruction>
